—ЩParchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/commands/docs/from_csv.mdЩ@8b179d9c3354429968ca708d3e619437457dfc1511a6a2ad1935dfcde1407eccҜtitle: from csv‘ҘFlagsЪ¬``--separator, -s {string}``
: A character to separate columns (either single char or 4 byte unicode sequence), defaults to ','.
``--comment, -c {string}``
: A comment character to ignore lines starting with it.
``--quote, -q {string}``
: A quote character to ignore separators in strings, defaults to '"'.
``--escape, -e {string}``
: An escape character for strings containing the quote character.
``--noheaders, -n``
: Don't treat the first row as column names.
``--flexible``
: Allow the number of fields in records to be variable.
``--no-infer``
: No field type inferencing.
``--trim, -t {string}``
: drop leading and trailing whitespaces around headers names and/or field values
’җҗЪШTitle: title: from csv
Path: Flags
Content:
``--separator, -s {string}``
: A character to separate columns (either single char or 4 byte unicode sequence), defaults to ','.
``--comment, -c {string}``
: A comment character to ignore lines starting with it.
``--quote, -q {string}``
: A quote character to ignore separators in strings, defaults to '"'.
``--escape, -e {string}``
: An escape character for strings containing the quote character.
``--noheaders, -n``
: Don't treat the first row as column names.
``--flexible``
: Allow the number of fields in records to be variable.
``--no-infer``
: No field type inferencing.
``--trim, -t {string}``
: drop leading and trailing whitespaces around headers names and/or field values
